    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290242m">
        <title>Step And Skirt Lights</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f082901166m" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g082901101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Step and Skirt Lights Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEP LIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SKIRT LIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SERVICE DOOR SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The
                <hotlnk xrefid="f082901166m">step and skirt lights</hotlnk>
                can be found near the service door of the bus.
            </para>
            <para>The step and skirt light system is a relay driver system dependant on the service door. When the
                service door is open the step and skirt lights will illuminate. When the service door is closed, the
                step and skirt lights will shut off.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
